name: Rowlet & Alolan Exeggutor-GX
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Grass Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. If that Pokémon is now a Stage 1 Pokémon, search your deck for a Stage 2 Pokémon that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Yanma
flavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won't miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes' heads instantly while flying by at high speed.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Celebi
flavorText: This Pokémon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.
Attack1Text: Devolve 1 of your opponent's evolved Pokémon by removing the highest Stage Evolution card from it. Your opponent shuffles that card into their deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Sewaddle and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Sewaddle
flavorText: This Pokémon makes clothes for itself. It chews up leaves and sews them with sticky thread extruded from its mouth.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Swadloon
flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Leavanny
flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.
Ability1Text: Your Grass Pokémon take 40 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance). You can't apply more than 1 Blanket Weaver Ability at a time.

name: Dwebble
flavorText: It makes a hole in a suitable rock. If that rock breaks, the Pokémon remains agitated until it locates a replacement.

name: Crustle
flavorText: It possesses legs of enormous strength, enabling it to carry heavy slabs for many days, even when crossing arid land.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 40 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 80 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Karrablast
flavorText: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Foongus
flavorText: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: They show off their Poké Ball caps to lure prey, but very few Pokémon are fooled by this.
Ability1Text: Whenever you play a Pokémon that has the Spore attack from your hand during your turn, you may leave your opponent's Active Pokémon Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Fomantis
flavorText: When the sun rises, Fomantis spreads its four leaves and bathes in the sunlight. The tip of its head has a pleasant aroma.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Lurantis
flavorText: For self-protection, it pretends to be a bug Pokémon. Both of its arms bear keen-edged petals.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Fire Energy attached to it, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: Because of its sweet, delicious aroma, bird Pokémon are always after it, but it's not intelligent enough to care.

name: Steenee
flavorText: It's protected by its hard sepals, so it plays with bird Pokémon without worry. They peck it relentlessly, but it doesn't care.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Tsareena
flavorText: A master of grand and beautiful kicks, it can knock out even kickboxing champions with a single blow.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Grass Energy card from your discard pile to your Active Pokémon.

name: Dhelmise
flavorText: It wraps its prey in green seaweed and sucks away their vitality. It only likes to go after big prey like Wailord.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Magmar
flavorText: Its entire body is burning. When it breathes, the temperature rises. When it sneezes, flames shoot out!
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Magmortar
flavorText: There are still quite a few factories that rely on the flames provided by Magmortar to process metals.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Numel
flavorText: Its humped back stores intensely hot magma. In rain, the magma cools, slowing its movement.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Camerupt
flavorText: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years—or whenever it becomes really angry.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Heatran-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokémon moves from your Bench to become your Active Pokémon, you may move any number of Fire Energy from your other Pokémon to it.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the amount of Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards of different types and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Litwick
flavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Litwick
flavorText: While shining a light and pretending to be a guide, it leeches off the life force of any who follow it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Lampent
flavorText: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: Being consumed in Chandelure's flame burns up the spirit, leaving the body behind.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 5 cards of your deck. This attack does 60 more damage for each Pokémon you discarded in this way. Then, put any number of Fire Pokémon you discarded in this way onto your Bench.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: It scatters embers in the tall grass. Then bug Pokémon, frightened by the flames, come flying out, and Fletchinder gobbles them up.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: Its tough wings don't allow fire to pass through them. A long time ago, firefighters' outfits were made from Talonflame wings.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Salandit
flavorText: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can't evolve.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.

name: Slowpoke & Psyduck-GX
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Supporter cards from your hand. This attack does 40 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage. If this Pokémon has at least 6 extra Water Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), flip 10 coins instead, and this attack does 100 more damage for each heads. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Lapras
flavorText: It likes swimming around with people on its back. In the Alola region, it's an important means of transportation over water.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put a Misty's Favor card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It feeds mainly on ice and snow. It's only able to survive in a limited number of places in the warm Alola region.

name: Froslass
flavorText: It freezes hikers who have come to climb snowy mountains and carries them back to its home. It only goes after men it thinks are handsome.
Attack1Text: Put up to 7 damage counters on this Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter you placed in this way.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Finneon
flavorText: When night falls, their pink patterns begin to shine. They're popular with divers, so there are resorts that feed them to keep them close.

name: Lumineon
flavorText: Deep down at the bottom of the ocean, prey is scarce. Lumineon get into fierce disputes with Lanturn over food.
Attack1Text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Snover
flavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Abomasnow
flavorText: It blankets wide areas in snow by whipping up blizzards. It is also known as "The Ice Monster."
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has any Water Energy attached to it, it is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Basculin
flavorText: Savage, violent Pokémon, red and blue Basculin are always fighting each other over territory.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each Basculin you have in play to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Tirtouga
flavorText: It was restored from an ancient fossil. Tirtouga lived in the sea but came up onto the land to search for prey.

name: Carracosta
flavorText: Its jaws are terrifyingly powerful. It could eat Omastar and Omanyte whole and not be bothered in the slightest by their shells.
Ability1Text: Pokémon Tool cards attached to your opponent's Pokémon have no effect.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Cryogonal
flavorText: They are born in snow clouds. They use chains made of ice crystals to capture prey.
Attack1Text: Your opponent can't play any Item cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Keldeo-GX
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon by your opponent's Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Dewpider
flavorText: When two Dewpider meet, they display their water bubbles to each other. Then the one with the smaller bubble gets out of the other's way.

name: Araquanid
flavorText: It usually passes its time in the water. When its belly is full, it stores its subdued prey in the water bubble on its head.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless more, and its Retreat Cost is Colorless more.

name: Wimpod
flavorText: It will pick up anything it finds on the ground. Sometimes it finds coins, so Murkrow and Meowth will go after it.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack doesn't happen.

name: Golisopod
flavorText: The shell covering its body is as hard as diamond. This Pokémon will do anything it takes to win.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has 2 or fewer Energy attached to it, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Pyukumuku
flavorText: The tradition known as Pyukumuku chucking started from the custom of throwing Pyukumuku back into the sea after they wash onshore.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Tapu Fini
flavorText: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has any Ultra Beasts in play, this attack can be used for Colorless.

name: Raichu & Alolan Raichu-GX
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 80 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Lightning Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 100 more damage. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, draw a card.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Its nature is to store up electricity. Forests where nests of Pikachu live are dangerous, since the trees are so often struck by lightning.

name: Alolan Raichu
flavorText: It focuses psychic energy into its tail and rides it like it's surfing. Another name for this Pokémon is "hodad."
Attack1Text: Discard any amount of Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. Then, for each Energy you discarded in this way, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon and do 30 damage to it. (You can choose the same Pokémon more than once.) This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Magnemite
flavorText: It's frequently the cause of power outages, which is why some power plants send out electrical signals that it can't stand.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Magneton
flavorText: Delicate equipment can malfunction in areas inhabited by Magneton, which send out mysterious electrical signals.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Magnezone
flavorText: It uses radar to monitor its territory. Intruders are quickly disposed of with a hyper beam.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in play, it is Lightning and Metal type.
Attack1Text: Put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock, they leisurely consume it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Also apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.
Attack1Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: With their sucker mouths, they suck in prey. Then they use their fangs to shock the prey with electricity.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is in your hand and you have at least 4 Lightning Energy cards in play, you may play this Pokémon onto your Bench. If you do, move any number of Lightning Energy from your other Pokémon to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.
Attack1Text: If, before doing damage, your opponent's Active Pokémon has more remaining HP than this Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Thundurus
flavorText: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: If Tornadus is on your Bench, this attack does 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Tapu Koko
flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Ultra Beast, this attack does 100 more damage, and discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Xurkitree
flavorText: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has exactly 3 Prize cards remaining, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Mewtwo & Mew-GX
Ability1Text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX on your Bench or in your discard pile. (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)
Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has at least 1 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Espeon & Deoxys-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your Benched Psychic Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Put 10 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like. If this Pokémon has at least 3 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), put 20 damage counters on them instead. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: It engages its enemies using psychic powers. Each of its three heads fires off psychokinetic energy, tripling its power.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Discard your hand.

name: Alolan Marowak
flavorText: The rich greenery of the Alola region is hard on Marowak. It controls fire to stay alive.
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck. If the card you discarded is a Pokémon, this attack does damage equal to that Pokémon's HP to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Jynx
flavorText: It sways its hips to a rhythm all its own. The precise movements of Jynx living in Alola are truly wonderful.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Wynaut
flavorText: It tends to move in a pack with others. They cluster in a tight group to sleep in a cave.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Latios-GX
Ability1Text: If you have 4 or fewer Pokémon in play, this Pokémon can't attack.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from TAG TEAM Pokémon.
Attack2Text: For the rest of this game, your opponent can't use any GX attacks. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Jirachi-GX
Ability1Text: Don't apply Psychic Weakness when Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) take damage from attacks.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Psychic Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Jirachi-GX
Ability1Text: Don't apply Psychic Weakness when Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) take damage from attacks.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Psychic Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Drifloon
flavorText: Its round body is stuffed with souls and expands each time it leads someone away.

name: Drifblim
flavorText: There's a rumor that if you catch a Drifblim floating on the wind at dusk, you'll be carried away to the afterlife.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch your Active TAG TEAM Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Skorupi
flavorText: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Uxie
flavorText: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.
Ability1Text: If you have Mesprit and Azelf in play, apply Weakness for each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) as ×4 instead.

name: Mesprit
flavorText: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Azelf
flavorText: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Giratina
flavorText: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Cresselia
flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard a Psychic Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Munna
flavorText: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Musharna
flavorText: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Both Active Pokémon are now Asleep. During your next turn, this Pokémon's attacks do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Elgyem
flavorText: It controls tremendous psychic power. Most reports of alien sightings are actually just people mistaking Elgyem for an alien.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: With its psychic powers, it rewrites its opponents' memories. You, too, may have already had your memories rewritten.
Attack2Text: Shuffle this Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your deck. Your opponent can't play any Item cards from their hand during their next turn.

name: Honedge
flavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Honedge
flavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Doublade
flavorText: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Aegislash
flavorText: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, put it into your hand instead of the discard pile. (Discard all cards attached to it.)
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage for each Item card in your discard pile. You can't do more than 130 damage in this way.

name: Mareanie
flavorText: They eat Corsola branches, so Mareanie are hated by craftsmen who work with Corsola branches that have naturally fallen off.

name: Toxapex
flavorText: To attack, this Pokémon sends toxic spikes flying at its enemies. Ones that come close get mown down by the claws on its feet.

name: Salandit
flavorText: The males will do whatever the females tell them. They give the females most of their food. Due to malnutrition, the males can't evolve.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: Salazzle lives deep in caves and forces the Salandit it has attracted with its pheromones to serve it.

name: Cosmog
flavorText: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.

name: Necrozma
flavorText: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached to it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Poipole
flavorText: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.
Attack2Text: If each player has exactly 1 Prize card remaining, this attack does 130 more damage.

name: Onix
flavorText: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Steelix
flavorText: Tempered underground under high pressure and heat, its body is harder than any metal.
Attack1Text: Attach 2 Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, your Pokémon can't attack. (This includes Pokémon that come into play on that turn.)

name: Cubone
flavorText: At night, it weeps loudly for its dead mother, but those cries only attract its natural enemy—Mandibuzz.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Aerodactyl-GX
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Basic Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless more.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Heracross
flavorText: It's proud of its thick horn. In Alola, its biggest rival is Vikavolt, which it's always fighting with.
Attack1Text: If 1 of your opponent's Pokémon used a GX attack during their last turn, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into their deck.

name: Breloom
flavorText: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Asleep, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon can't use Spirited Headbutt during your next turn.

name: Medicham
flavorText: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.
Attack1Text: Put 4 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has a Karate Belt card attached to it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: Thought to have gone extinct, Relicanth was given a name that is a variation of the name of the person who discovered it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Trainer card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Gible
flavorText: It reacts to anything that moves—flies right at it and bites it. Sometimes it injures itself, but it doesn't care too much.

name: Gabite
flavorText: It loves shiny things. When it finds a Sableye trying to catch a Carbink, Gabite becomes furiously angry and attacks the Sableye.

name: Garchomp
flavorText: It flies at the speed of sound while searching for prey, and it has midair battles with Salamence as the two compete for food.
Ability1Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this Pokémon's attacks do 80 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: You may discard an Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It knows how people and Pokémon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn't approach dangerous opponents.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It knows how people and Pokémon feel by looking at their auras. It doesn't approach dangerous opponents.

name: Lucario
flavorText: It concentrates its mental energy and fires off mysterious waves called auras, which can crush boulders of large size to dust.
Ability1Text: Your TAG TEAM Pokémon take 20 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It makes its way swiftly through the soil by putting both claws together and rotating at high speed.

name: Excadrill
flavorText: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.
Attack1Text: Shuffle 4 cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Archen
flavorText: Once thought to be the ancestor of all bird Pokémon, some of the latest research suggests that may not be the case.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Archeops
flavorText: This ancient Pokémon's plumage is delicate, so if anyone other than an experienced professional tries to restore it, they will fail.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: Its charge is strong enough to break through a giant castle wall in one blow. This Pokémon is spoken of in legends.
Attack1Text: If all of your Benched Pokémon have at least 1 damage counter on them, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Meloetta
flavorText: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.
Attack1Text: Attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your TAG TEAM Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: This is Zygarde when about 10% of its pieces have been assembled. It leaps at its opponent's chest and sinks its sharp fangs into them.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, your Zygarde's and Zygarde-GX's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Attach a Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Umbreon & Darkrai-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon-GX or Benched Pokémon-EX. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from their hand during their next turn. If this Pokémon has at least 5 extra Darkness Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Mega Sableye & Tyranitar-GX
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 1 more Prize card.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has at least 5 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), discard the top 15 cards of your opponent's deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Alolan Grimer
flavorText: There are a hundred or so of them living in Alola's waste-disposal site. They're all hard workers who eat a lot of trash.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: It has a weakness for shiny things. It's been known to sneak into the nests of Gabite—noted collectors of jewels—in search of treasure.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: It has a weakness for shiny things. It's been known to sneak into the nests of Gabite—noted collectors of jewels—in search of treasure.

name: Honchkrow
flavorText: It will absolutely not forgive failure from or betrayal by its goons. It has no choice in this if it wants to maintain the order of the flock.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Sneasel
flavorText: They will cooperate to steal eggs from the nests of bird Pokémon, but fights break out to determine which one gets to eat the eggs.

name: Weavile-GX
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a basic Darkness Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for any number of Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Sableye
flavorText: It digs through the ground with its hard claws and crunches down gems with its thick pointy teeth. Carbink is its favorite food.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if it is Knocked Out), put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Drapion
flavorText: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: Its cute act is a ruse. When victims let down their guard, they find their items taken. It attacks with sharp claws.
Attack1Text: Discard a Pokémon Tool card from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Liepard
flavorText: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon is a Basic Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: They move in small groups, walking around lazily. Anyone who makes eye contact gets smacked with a headbutt.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: This Pokémon may be rude, but it takes very good care of its family, its friends, and its turf.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your remaining Prize cards.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
Attack1Text: If there is any Stadium card in play, this attack does 20 more damage.
Attack2Text: Put 3 damage counters on 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon that has an Ability.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Mawile-GX
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand onto your Bench during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand and put any number of Basic Pokémon you find there onto their Bench.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Discard all Supporter cards you find there. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Escavalier
flavorText: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has no damage counters on it before this attack does damage, this attack does nothing.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can't move as well.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: This nuisance sneaks into people's homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: It sneaks into people's homes and steals electricity from their outlets. When your electric bill seems off, it's the handiwork of this rascal.
Attack1Text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Garchomp & Giratina-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It's still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Dratini
flavorText: It's still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Water Energy attached to it, it has no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: Lakes where Dragonair live are filled with offerings from people, because they believe this Pokémon is able to control the weather.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If both of them are tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: Lakes where Dragonair live are filled with offerings from people, because they believe this Pokémon is able to control the weather.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It flies over raging seas as if they were nothing. Observing this, a ship's captain dubbed this Pokémon "the sea incarnate."
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Water Energy card, a Lightning Energy card, or 1 of each from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack1Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Dragonite-GX
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Latias
flavorText: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon to that Pokémon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Axew
flavorText: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokémon.

name: Fraxure
flavorText: Their tusks can shatter rocks. Territory battles between Fraxure can be intensely violent.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Haxorus
flavorText: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard any Stadium card in play. If you do, attach up to 3 in any combination of Fire and Metal Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage times the amount of basic Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: The red skin on its face is harder than rock. In narrow caves, it squares off against its enemies and charges face-first right into them.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to the new Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Noibat
flavorText: Fruits are its favorite foods. This gourmet carefully picks out just the ripe ones using its sonar.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Noivern
flavorText: Although it has a violent disposition, if you give it a nice ripe fruit that it loves, Noivern will suddenly become tame.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Discard the top card of your deck.

name: Naganadel-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard an Ultra Beast card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 170 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Add a card from your opponent's discard pile to their Prize cards face down. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Lickitung
flavorText: It checks out whatever's around it by licking everything. If you don't clean off a spot where it's licked you, you'll break out in a rash!
Attack1Text: Draw a card for each of your Pokémon in play that has a Retreat Cost of exactly 4.

name: Lickilicky
flavorText: A contest is under way to determine which one can stick its tongue out the farthest. The current record is…more than 82 feet.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand, discard the top card of your opponent's deck, and discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: Kangaskhan protects its child by keeping it in its pouch. It has zero forgiveness for those who harm its child and will beat them down.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your TAG TEAM Pokémon in play.

name: Tauros
flavorText: They live in groups. The one with the longest, thickest, and most-scarred horns is the boss of the herd.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: Every day, it tilts its head in the same rhythm. A long time ago, people raised these Pokémon to serve as clocks.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Noctowl
flavorText: With eyes that can see in pitch-darkness, it never lets its prey escape. Some even call it "the emperor of dark nights."
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Slakoth
flavorText: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if they attach an Energy card from their hand to the Defending Pokémon, their turn ends.

name: Slakoth
flavorText: The way Slakoth lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Vigoroth
flavorText: Its heartbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can't sit still for one second.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Slaking
flavorText: The world's laziest Pokémon. It moves to another spot when there's no food left within its reach.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 4 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack1Text: You may do 100 more damage. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 100 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Bidoof
flavorText: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Bibarel
flavorText: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to this Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Munchlax
flavorText: It hides food under its long fur, but it sometimes forgets about it and causes a stinky disturbance.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, put a card from your discard pile on top of your deck. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.

name: Pidove
flavorText: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.

name: Tranquill
flavorText: Many people believe that, deep in the forest where Tranquill live, there is a peaceful place where there is no war.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Unfezant
flavorText: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females' flying abilities surpass those of the males.
Attack2Text: You may have each player shuffle all cards attached to their Active Pokémon into their deck.

name: Audino
flavorText: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, you may draw a card.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Tornadus
flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.
Attack2Text: If Thundurus is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Fletchling
flavorText: While it's an amiable Pokémon, if you touch it unexpectedly, it will heat up its body in an instant, and you'll be burned.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: Its stomach takes up most of its long torso. It's a big eater, so the amount Trainers have to spend on its food is no laughing matter.

name: Gumshoos
flavorText: Although it wasn't originally found in Alola, this Pokémon was brought over a long time ago when there was a huge Rattata outbreak.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon-GX or Pokémon-EX, this attack's base damage is 30.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: It normally spends its time meditating in the treetops. It throws Poké Balls and gives other Pokémon orders as it pleases.
Attack1Text: Put a Pokémon from your hand face down in front of you. Your opponent guesses the type of that Pokémon, and then you reveal it. If your opponent guessed right, they draw 4 cards. If they guessed wrong, you draw 4 cards. Return the Pokémon to your hand.

name: Type: Null
flavorText: A Pokémon weapon developed for a specific mission, it went berserk during an experiment, so it was cryogenically frozen.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Silvally
flavorText: This is its form once it has awakened and evolved. Freed from its heavy mask, its speed is greatly increased.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card your opponent took on their last turn.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Komala
flavorText: It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon remains Asleep between turns, put 6 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Flyinium Z: Air Slash
Attack1Text: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Normalium Z: Tackle
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the amount of Fire Energy attached to this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Lightning Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 100 more damage. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack1Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 80 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Lightning Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 100 more damage. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

Attack1Text: If this Pokémon has at least 1 extra Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), heal all damage from all of your Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)
